ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You'll spend most of class time listening to presentations of other students/ giving feedback and detailing plans for the thesis show. It's amazing with Lisa.

Very helpful (especially artist statement). Definitely could've started group crits on senior project earlier though. Also first semester was not helpful at all. Wish we could've worked with Lisa and done group crits starting first semester

Obviously you have to take this, but it's a good course! Hopefully your previous two seminars were better than ours were, but you'll finally get to collaborate on other majors' work and learn about artist statements, presenting on yourself, etc.
It's required, but it's one of the better required art major courses that I've taken. Lisa is great, and it's nice to actually get to know the other majors in your year and their work.
